cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.AI

The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques to recover the 3D shape and motion of animals from video. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of deep learning methods, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also deals with the optimization of joint correspondences, which falls under the category of cs.GR (Graphics). The use of energy minimization techniques to fit a detailed 3D model to the image makes cs.RO (Robotics) another possible category. Finally, the paper involves the use of synthetic data to train the joint candidate predictor, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
